Package sandra.libs.nlu.nlulib

Class Summary
Alternative Represents a rule in a speech grammar (see chapter 6 for an example)
GrammarElement Abstraction of the elements in a hand-crafted grammar, specifies the methods that are common to all the different element types.
HandCraftedGrammar Handcrafted speech grammar (see chapter 6)
Item Represents an item in the speech grammar (see chapter 6 for an example)
NLU Processes the output of the speech recognizer either with a statistical or a handcrafted grammar obtaining its semantic interpretation.
Repeat Represents an repeat element in the speech grammar (see chapter 6 for an example)
Rule Represents a rule in a speech grammar (see chapter 6 for an example)
RuleReference Represents the reference to a rule in the grammar (see chapter 6 for an example)
SemanticParsing Represents the semantic parsing for a phrase, including the position index that allows to determine the group of the regular expression that should match the text that triggers each tag.
 

Exception Summary
GrammarException Allows a more fine-grained management of exceptions, and to provide a possible reason to be communicated to the user
